Borough:
How Calculated:

Number of asthma-related hospitalizations among NYC resident children up to 4 years old.

Year: A hospitalization is included if it has an ICD-9 principal diagnosis code of 493 or an ICD-10 principal diagnosis code of J45. New York hospitals began using the ICD-10 system on October 1 2015. Because the ICD systems are similar in how they classify childhood asthma data can be compared across years.

Borough:
How Calculated:

Number of asthma-related hospitalizations among NYC resident children up to 4 years old divided by the population of children up to 4 years old using NYC DOHMH intercensal estimates; expressed as cases per 10000 residents.

Year: A hospitalization is included if it has an ICD-9 principal diagnosis code of 493 or an ICD-10 principal diagnosis code of J45. New York hospitals began using the ICD-10 system on October 1 2015. Because the ICD systems are similar in how they classify childhood asthma data can be compared across years.
NYC Department of Health and Mental Hygiene
